<p>I am prototyping by producing a more or less complete working version of one of the activities. If this works OK I&rsquo;ll rewrite the whole course in this way. I&rsquo;m prototyping my live demo using Jing to create a sceencast. &nbsp;&nbsp;[Note: Is this really a prototype?]</p>
<p><strong>Set goal</strong> &ndash; to understand how Grades work in Moodle</p>
<p><strong>Describe task</strong>: view Grader report, change number of rows, add two marks, create a grade item, export the gradebook and re-import.</p>
<p><strong>Tool </strong>&ndash; Moodle training course space</p>
<p><strong>Data collection</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Observe how users interact with the instructions, take notes of actions, timings and talk</li>
<li>Refer back to any interesting moments &ndash; especially any in which they vary from the designed activity - and ask what they were thinking at that moment or why they took that action.</li>
</ul>
<p>The activity is to understand how Grades work in Moodle</p>
<p>Elements required in prototype:</p>
<ul>
<li>Moodle course space with Grades pre-set up</li>
<li>Demo + Instructions to do some tasks within Moodle&rsquo;s Grades.</li>
</ul>]]></description>
